My meme

meme1 <- image_read(path='https://img.freepik.com/free-vector/simple-vibing-cat-square-meme_742173-4493.jpg?w=740&t=st=1709951033~exp=1709951633~hmac=26fa1d8a8aa151ea49277bb066c5583f070e8605631d82a08fe43198f0d02bdc')
meme1_scale <- image_scale(meme1,180) # change the size of image

meme2 <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRWjvvbcDgRtZiqBD6YT_J9Jic0LXmv-fDiSrM-P9GEfgxAHvKEH-wnd9s2cA&s")
meme2_scale <- image_scale(meme2,180) # change the size of image


blank1 <- image_blank(width = 180,height=180,color="#F0F0F0") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "calm down",
                 color = "#555",
                 size = 36,
                 font = "center")


blank2 <- image_blank(width = 180,height=180,color="#F0F0F0") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Failed",
                 color = "#555",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "center")

combin <- c(blank1,meme1_scale,meme2_scale,blank2)# make 3 image into 1 picture
combin_scale <- image_scale(combin,180)
final_image <- image_append(combin_scale)
final_image

animation <- combin_scale %>%
  image_animate(fps = 1)

image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
